      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The risk is that clarithromycin can increase the levels of simvastatin in your blood, which can lead to muscle breakdown, or rhabdomyolysis. This is a serious issue, not just mild nausea, so you should not take them without proper instruction. To be safe, you must check the specific interaction guidelines, but I strongly advise you to call your pharmacist right now for the correct timing protocol.",
